title.narrative: OUTPUT 6.1: SOCIAL POLICY AND PROTECTION

description.narrative: National institutions use equity-based information to develop child-sensitive policies and programme., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses (Covid), Equitable Access To Quality Education, Equitable Access To Quality Education (Covid), Evaluation And Research, Evaluation And Research (Covid), Social Protection, Social Protection (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, children, especially the poorest, the most excluded and those affected by crisis, have access to child-sensitive and shock- responsive social services, benefit from positive community practices and are empowered to be agents of change within their communities.
